00:21:41,885 --> 00:21:45,597
That boy's got
your granddaddy's eyes.

239
00:21:49,393 --> 00:21:52,020
Well, hon,

240
00:21:52,062 --> 00:21:54,189
I better get back.

241
00:21:54,273 --> 00:21:57,359
Looks like
there's a storm coming.

242
00:21:57,401 --> 00:22:00,779
No, Granny,
it... it's clear.

243
00:22:15,377 --> 00:22:19,131
Annie, always use
your instinct, honey.

244
00:22:48,577 --> 00:22:52,080
Now you tell Miss Francis
I'll be home by 9:30, okay?

245
00:22:52,164 --> 00:22:54,458
- Bring back something.
- All right, I promise.

246
00:22:54,541 --> 00:22:57,252
- I love you too, Mama.
- I know. And I love you too, hon.

247
00:22:57,377 --> 00:23:00,047
- Be good. Bye.
- Bye, Mama.

248
00:23:00,130 --> 00:23:02,508
You ready?

249
00:23:02,591 --> 00:23:04,843
I don't know why
I let you talk me into this.

250
00:23:04,927 --> 00:23:07,387
'Cause it's time you quit
living like a nun, that's why.

251
00:23:07,471 --> 00:23:11,141
Don't worry. You're going to be
the prettiest girl here, next to me.

252
00:23:11,225 --> 00:23:13,602
You still a married man?

253
00:23:13,685 --> 00:23:16,355
I don't know about that.

254
00:23:16,438 --> 00:23:20,526
- Oh, thank you.
- Thank you very much.

255
00:23:20,609 --> 00:23:23,862
- Do we pay him now or...
- I sign for it later.

256
00:23:23,946 --> 00:23:26,073
Is it good?

257
00:23:27,199 --> 00:23:29,535
- Annie, there he is.
- Who?

258
00:23:29,618 --> 00:23:32,830
That guy I... That guy I was
telling you about. Look at him.

259
00:23:32,913 --> 00:23:36,792
He's right over there by the bar.
Don't he look like Antonio Banderas?

260
00:23:36,875 --> 00:23:40,337
Oh, my God! He saw me! Shit!
He saw me staring at him.

261
00:23:40,420 --> 00:23:45,634
All right, get your cards out. Tell
me if he's gonna come over here.

262
00:23:45,717 --> 00:23:47,719
I don't have my cards with me.
I am off-duty.

263
00:23:47,803 --> 00:23:49,847
Hello, Mrs. Wilson.

264
00:23:49,930 --> 00:23:53,559
- It's Annie.
- Sit down. You're blocking my view.

265
00:23:55,769 --> 00:23:59,356
- Sorry. You remember Jessica?
- Hi, Annie.

266
00:23:59,439 --> 00:24:01,233
I didn't know you were a member
of the country club.

267
00:24:01,275 --> 00:24:04,403
I'm not.
I kind of tagged along with Linda.

268
00:24:04,444 --> 00:24:08,198
- How nice. It's a great outfit.
- Thank you.

269
00:24:08,282 --> 00:24:12,161
- What's Mike up to tonight?
- Moping around his baby-sitters.

270
00:24:12,244 --> 00:24:14,580
Yeah? He's...
He's a great kid.

271
00:24:14,621 --> 00:24:17,374
I was actually thinking you should
have him come down to school and...

272
00:24:17,457 --> 00:24:20,419
Come on, Wayne. Let's not talk
shop tonight, all right?

273
00:24:20,502 --> 00:24:22,588
- Let's just have fun.
- Okay.

274
00:24:22,629 --> 00:24:25,424
- Hi there, fun-seekers.
- Hey, there.

275
00:24:25,465 --> 00:24:28,677
- How about a dance with Daddy?
- Of course I will, handsome.

276
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:36,393
Mr. King, I don't know
if you know, Annie Wilson.

277
00:24:36,476 --> 00:24:40,355
Oh, yeah. Yeah.
I think I've seen you at church.

278
00:24:40,439 --> 00:24:44,276
- That is quite a dress, Miss Linda.
- I'm glad somebody noticed.

279
00:24:44,359 --> 00:24:48,947
- You want to give it a try?
- Oh, no. No, I don't think so.

280
00:24:48,989 --> 00:24:50,282
No, thank you.

281
00:24:50,324 --> 00:24:54,203
Come on. I asked you to dance,
not walk on hot coals.

282
00:24:54,286 --> 00:24:56,955
When was the last time
you danced?

283
00:24:56,997 --> 00:24:59,625
I think it's so long,
I've forgotten how to do it.

284
00:24:59,708 --> 00:25:03,921
Well, I'll make you look good then,
'cause I'm a terrible dancer.

285
00:25:05,339 --> 00:25:07,591
Wayne.

286
00:25:07,674 --> 00:25:10,135
I'll dance.

287
00:25:12,846 --> 00:25:14,806
- Good luck.
- Yeah.

288
00:25:14,890 --> 00:25:18,101
Missed your big chance.

289
00:25:38,831 --> 00:25:41,250
Thank you.

290
00:25:55,722 --> 00:25:57,641
Somebody
might come in here.

291
00:25:57,724 --> 00:26:00,477
I guess you
better fuck me fast.

292
00:26:14,283 --> 00:26:16,702
You having a good time?

293
00:26:19,288 --> 00:26:22,040
Me neither.

294
00:26:27,087 --> 00:26:29,256
You seen Jessica around?

295
00:26:30,924 --> 00:26:35,137
She up and disappeared on me again.
She's got a way of doing that.

296
00:26:38,557 --> 00:26:43,020
- What do you think of Jessica?
- She's... She's very beautiful.

297
00:26:43,103 --> 00:26:46,732
Yeah, the main thing
about her, she's just...

298
00:26:46,773 --> 00:26:49,276
so full of life.

299
00:26:49,318 --> 00:26:52,112
We're a little different
in that respect.

300
00:26:52,196 --> 00:26:55,073
Oh.
I'm used to tennis shoes.

301
00:27:01,371 --> 00:27:03,373
This kind of reminds me
when I was a kid.

302
00:27:03,457 --> 00:27:06,668
I'd sit out on that porch.

303
00:27:06,752 --> 00:27:09,922
I'd have so many thoughts,
just couldn't count 'em.

304
00:27:10,005 --> 00:27:12,090
How'd you
wind up in Brixton?

305
00:27:12,132 --> 00:27:15,093
My husband. He got a job here
at the cable plant.

306
00:27:16,303 --> 00:27:18,263
Right.

307
00:27:20,974 --> 00:27:22,935
What?

308
00:27:25,145 --> 00:27:28,273
Did... Did you know...

309
00:27:28,315 --> 00:27:31,527
something was going
to happen to your husband?

310
00:27:35,113 --> 00:27:37,533
In an E.S.P. kind of way?

311
00:27:40,327 --> 00:27:44,206
- Well, I don't know...
- You don't believe in it.

312
00:27:46,959 --> 00:27:49,086
I don't know.
I guess I just...

313
00:27:51,338 --> 00:27:53,465
I don't believe there
are any great mysteries in life.

314
00:27:53,507 --> 00:27:56,552
I kind of figure what
you see is what you get.

315
00:28:01,974 --> 00:28:04,434
Well,

316
00:28:04,518 --> 00:28:07,312
I didn't know that there
was going to be an explosion.

317
00:28:07,396 --> 00:28:11,316
But... the night before,
I had this real bad,

318
00:28:11,358 --> 00:28:13,485
bad dream, you know.

319
00:28:13,527 --> 00:28:16,405
I dreamt that I was all by myself.
That Ben...

320
00:28:16,488 --> 00:28:20,117
He wasn't
around anymore and...

321
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:23,328
tried to stop him going to work
the next day, but...

322
00:28:27,583 --> 00:28:29,960
So you can't keep
a good man from work, right?

323
00:28:36,758 --> 00:28:39,344
You kind
of remind me of him.

324
00:28:42,097 --> 00:28:44,683
Wayne?

325
00:28:44,725 --> 00:28:48,187
- I've been looking for you.
- I've been right here.

326
00:28:50,564 --> 00:28:52,691
I see.

327
00:28:55,027 --> 00:28:57,154
- Hi.
- Hi.

328
00:28:57,237 --> 00:29:00,073
Let's go talk to Daddy.
He's feeling real depressed tonight.

329
00:29:00,157 --> 00:29:02,034
That big deal
he's working on went bad.

330
00:29:02,075 --> 00:29:05,078
Oh, we got a major crisis
here, Annie. Excuse us?

331
00:29:06,205 --> 00:29:08,332
- Okay.
- Bye.

332
00:29:10,334 --> 00:29:12,461
See you later, alligator.

333
00:29:12,586 --> 00:29:15,088
- In a while, crocodile.
- Good night, boys.

334
00:29:15,172 --> 00:29:17,216
Go to sleep for Mama.

335
00:29:18,383 --> 00:29:20,969
- What's that, hon?
- Blueberry muffins.

336
00:29:21,053 --> 00:29:23,430
Whatcha doin' with muffins
in your pockets?

337
00:29:23,514 --> 00:29:25,557
Miss Francis cooked them.

338
00:29:25,641 --> 00:29:27,893
Yeah, but what are they
doing in your pockets?

339
00:29:27,976 --> 00:29:31,980
They're in my pockets 'cause I put
'em there when she wasn't looking...

340
00:29:32,064 --> 00:29:34,233
so I didn't
have to eat them.

341
00:29:34,274 --> 00:29:38,320
Her blueberry muffins is terrible.

342
00:29:41,073 --> 00:29:43,992
Y'all wait here a minute.
Take Ben, hon.

343
00:31:12,956 --> 00:31:16,919
When God's fighting for you,
every soldier's important.

344
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:19,963
When God's fighting for you,
every soldier's important.

345
00:31:20,047 --> 00:31:22,341
God does not give
one to the Devil.

346
00:31:22,424 --> 00:31:24,801
If every child of God
obeyed God,

347
00:31:24,885 --> 00:31:26,803
the Devil cannot
wipe you out.

348
00:31:26,887 --> 00:31:29,097
He cannot take you out
before your time.

349
00:31:29,139 --> 00:31:31,099
If you obey God,
I don't care what the Devil...

350
00:31:31,141 --> 00:31:35,771
has placed upon your life,
Jesus can deliver you.

351
00:31:35,854 --> 00:31:39,441
Jesus came to bring you
out of your prison house.

352
00:31:39,525 --> 00:31:43,445
- Mama, is everything okay?
- Yeah, everything's fine.

353
00:31:43,487 --> 00:31:47,199
- You sure?
- Yeah. Time for you to go to bed.

354
00:31:49,952 --> 00:31:53,247
I know him. He's
a squirrel-hunting buddy of mine.

355
00:31:53,330 --> 00:31:56,917
- But I don't think that Donnie...
- I'm telling you it was him.

356
00:31:57,000 --> 00:32:00,128
What makes you think he'd want
to bust into your house?

357
00:32:00,212 --> 00:32:03,257
Well, his wife,
she's a client of mine,

358
00:32:03,340 --> 00:32:06,468
and he thinks I'm trying
to break up their marriage.

359
00:32:06,510 --> 00:32:08,929
Are you?

360
00:32:09,012 --> 00:32:12,599
Listen,
Donnie's high-strung.

361
00:32:12,683 --> 00:32:15,352
You know,
ain't no doubt about that.

362
00:32:15,435 --> 00:32:18,021
But I don't think he's the one
that busted into your house.

363
00:32:18,105 --> 00:32:21,441
Listen, I appreciate the coffee
and everything. Take care.

364
00:32:29,658 --> 00:32:33,412
I just can't get through
a wall of some kind in my head...

365
00:32:33,495 --> 00:32:36,665
or... or my soul.

366
00:32:36,707 --> 00:32:39,168
Sometimes I don't
even know the difference...

367
00:32:39,209 --> 00:32:42,379
between my head or my soul.

368
00:32:42,462 --> 00:32:45,174
I think everybody
has that trouble, Buddy.

369
00:32:48,844 --> 00:32:51,054
All right.

370
00:32:56,185 --> 00:32:58,478
Your daddy...

371
00:32:58,562 --> 00:33:02,357
He took things
away from you when you...

372
00:33:02,441 --> 00:33:04,902
when you were a little boy.

373
00:33:07,070 --> 00:33:09,865
Do you understand that?

374
00:33:11,700 --> 00:33:17,039
He... He seen me playing around with
something, like a toy or something,

375
00:33:17,122 --> 00:33:20,167
he'd just
take it away from me.

376
00:33:20,250 --> 00:33:22,878
Did he take other things
away from you?

377
00:33:29,134 --> 00:33:31,678
Buddy...

378
00:33:31,762 --> 00:33:33,889
You got to find out, hon,

379
00:33:33,931 --> 00:33:37,226
why you hate him so much.

380
00:33:37,267 --> 00:33:40,562
My daddy's a good man.
I don't hate my dad.

381
00:33:41,813 --> 00:33:44,024
He's good to Mama and me.

382
00:33:46,777 --> 00:33:50,614
Every kid needs a hit with a belt
sometime. I mean...

383
00:33:50,697 --> 00:33:55,202
Buddy, you got to try to get past
this wall that you're talking about.

384
00:33:56,495 --> 00:33:58,455
Hon, you need to talk
about your daddy.

385
00:33:58,539 --> 00:34:01,917
Why don't you tell me why I hate
him? You're the goddamn psychic!

386
00:34:01,959 --> 00:34:05,420
Huh?
You're the goddamn psychic!

387
00:34:24,022 --> 00:34:26,775
I think I better go.

388
00:34:26,859 --> 00:34:29,153
I have to go home,

389
00:34:32,823 --> 00:34:34,783
right now.

390
00:34:34,867 --> 00:34:37,661
I'm sorry
I yelled at you.

391
00:34:37,744 --> 00:34:39,788
It's all right.

392
00:34:41,123 --> 00:34:43,792
I just need...
I just need your help.

393
00:34:46,837 --> 00:34:50,132
I just keep thinking about that blue
diamond. I keep thinking about...

394
00:34:50,215 --> 00:34:55,137
Buddy, if you think about these
things in your childhood, hon,

395
00:34:55,179 --> 00:34:59,266
and you face up to them,
then I will be able to help you.

396
00:35:01,560 --> 00:35:03,812
I know, hon.
I just...

397
00:35:03,854 --> 00:35:07,274
I think you got to do
some thinking on your own.

398
00:35:09,735 --> 00:35:11,695
Okay.

399
00:35:11,737 --> 00:35:14,781
Oh. You...

400
00:35:14,865 --> 00:35:16,783
I'll help you there.

401
00:35:16,867 --> 00:35:20,245
- Okay, you put it up there.
- Hey, Ben.

402
00:35:20,329 --> 00:35:23,123
- Hello?
- You got a lot of pretty things.

403
00:35:23,207 --> 00:35:25,667
I liked looking at them.

404
00:35:25,709 --> 00:35:28,128
You ever seen anybody
skin a squirrel?

405
00:35:28,212 --> 00:35:30,964
You stick a knife
in its belly and zip.

406
00:35:31,048 --> 00:35:33,300
That's what I'm going to do
to you and your children...

407
00:35:33,383 --> 00:35:35,469
you ever call
the police again.

408
00:35:35,552 --> 00:35:37,513
I did not.

409
00:35:50,859 --> 00:35:52,903
Mama?

410
00:35:54,738 --> 00:35:56,949
Hey.

411
00:35:57,032 --> 00:36:00,828
- How come you're not asleep?
- I don't know.

412
00:36:03,580 --> 00:36:05,874
- What's that bat for?
- Oh.

413
00:36:05,916 --> 00:36:09,878
Don't worry, honey.
I'm... I'm just working on my swing.

414
00:36:11,713 --> 00:36:16,051
How come we never go
to the cemetery and see Daddy?

415
00:36:16,093 --> 00:36:20,097
Well, we went out there
just last month on his birthday.

416
00:36:21,348 --> 00:36:23,892
Honey, I'm real busy,
you know that.

417
00:36:23,934 --> 00:36:26,728
Well, it seems like you have time
for a lot of strangers.

418
00:36:26,812 --> 00:36:30,190
If we're talking about my
appointments, they're not strangers.

419
00:36:30,274 --> 00:36:32,651
They're the ones
that put food on our table.

420
00:36:32,734 --> 00:36:35,195
But how come we don't
even talk about Daddy?

421
00:36:35,279 --> 00:36:37,614
Go on, Mike.
I'm trying to read.

422
00:37:45,557 --> 00:37:47,684
- Annie?
- We're going to have to frame that.

423
00:37:47,768 --> 00:37:49,728
- It's just a painting.
- That's beautiful.

424
00:37:49,811 --> 00:37:52,648
- Annie.
- Hey.

425
00:37:52,731 --> 00:37:56,235
Hey, listen. I know why Kenneth King
wasn't in church today.

426
00:37:56,318 --> 00:38:00,280
- Put your belt on. Why?
- 'Cause his daughter disappeared.

427
00:38:00,364 --> 00:38:02,241
Jessica?

428
00:38:02,324 --> 00:38:04,243
What do you mean
she disappeared?

429
00:38:04,326 --> 00:38:06,912
Well, Kenneth woke up this morning
and Jessica wasn't there,

430
00:38:06,995 --> 00:38:08,664
and her bed
hadn't even been slept in.

431
00:38:08,747 --> 00:38:11,083
Annie, you think
she ran off?

432
00:38:11,166 --> 00:38:13,585
I know her and Wayne were
supposed to be married in June.

433
00:38:13,669 --> 00:38:16,588
- Maybe she got cold feet.
- Maybe.

434
00:38:16,672 --> 00:38:19,466
Maybe this will clear
the way for you and Wayne.

435
00:38:20,676 --> 00:38:23,178
- What are you talking about?
- Oh, come on.

436
00:38:23,262 --> 00:38:26,807
I saw the way y'all were looking
at each other Friday night.

437
00:38:26,890 --> 00:38:29,351
Y'all both just
had stars in your eyes.

438
00:38:29,393 --> 00:38:31,854
Oh, Linda, that's nuts.

439
00:38:31,895 --> 00:38:35,691
- Yeah. Annie, love is nuts.
- Come on. Go home.

440
00:38:35,732 --> 00:38:39,194
Listen,
I want you to get some rest.

441
00:38:39,278 --> 00:38:41,822
You look terrible, okay?
Bye, boys.

442
00:38:41,905 --> 00:38:44,366
- I got to go.
- Bye, Miss Linda.

443
00:38:59,047 --> 00:39:01,383
Ben, get your hand
out of there!

444
00:39:01,425 --> 00:39:03,385
That's for y'all's
cake tonight.

445
00:39:03,427 --> 00:39:06,847
- What am I gonna ice the cake with?
- I like icin', Mama.

446
00:39:06,889 --> 00:39:09,308
Yeah,
I can see that, punkin.

447
00:39:09,391 --> 00:39:11,351
Miller!

448
00:39:12,811 --> 00:39:14,730
Miller, hon, would you
go ask Miss Francis...

449
00:39:14,813 --> 00:39:17,399
if she's got another
can of icing, please?

450
00:39:17,482 --> 00:39:20,110
- Mama!
- I'm coming, Ben.

451
00:39:41,590 --> 00:39:44,343
Where you going, son?

452
00:39:48,972 --> 00:39:51,225
You wanna ride
in the truck?

453
00:39:54,311 --> 00:39:58,440
I got a question for you.
You know my wife Valerie?

454
00:39:58,524 --> 00:40:01,068
She been around
to see your mama lately?

455
00:40:02,361 --> 00:40:05,572
Hey, boy,
I asked you a question.

456
00:40:07,366 --> 00:40:09,409
Get my hat.

457
00:40:16,208 --> 00:40:19,044
You know, I feel sorry
for you and your brothers.

458
00:40:19,127 --> 00:40:22,089
I mean, your mama
being a witch and all.

459
00:40:22,130 --> 00:40:24,466
If she don't stop
her evil ways,

460
00:40:24,550 --> 00:40:27,010
some day somebody's
gonna burn her up.

461
00:40:27,094 --> 00:40:30,055
And then you boys
are gonna be without a daddy...

462
00:40:30,138 --> 00:40:32,599
or a mama.

463
00:40:32,683 --> 00:40:36,562
Hey, Miller?
You all right?

464
00:40:36,645 --> 00:40:39,940
He said mama's a witch
and they're gonna burn her up.

465
00:40:39,982 --> 00:40:41,984
Oh, he did?

466
00:40:46,905 --> 00:40:50,367
- You better mind your own business.
- I intend to, Donnie.

467
00:40:58,584 --> 00:41:00,586
Motherfucker!

468
00:41:00,669 --> 00:41:03,130
Goddamn it! Fuck!

469
00:41:03,172 --> 00:41:05,174
Look, fucker!

470
00:41:06,884 --> 00:41:08,844
Shoot me!
Shoot me!

471
00:41:08,886 --> 00:41:11,471
Shoot me,
you motherfucker!

472
00:41:11,555 --> 00:41:14,516
Shoot me! Shoot me!

473
00:41:31,533 --> 00:41:33,827
You all right?

474
00:41:45,839 --> 00:41:48,675
Tuscan Rouge.

475
00:41:48,759 --> 00:41:50,886
What was I thinking?

476
00:41:53,555 --> 00:41:55,849
I want icin', Mama.

477
00:41:55,891 --> 00:41:58,018
Hon, you've had icing enough
to put you in a coma.

478
00:41:58,060 --> 00:42:00,062
And from now on,

479
00:42:00,103 --> 00:42:02,064
I want to know where you all are
every minute of the day.

480
00:42:02,147 --> 00:42:04,274
All right?

481
00:42:05,692 --> 00:42:08,278
Mike, I'm gonna start
driving you and Miller to school.

482
00:42:09,988 --> 00:42:12,699
I wish Daddy was here.

483
00:42:12,741 --> 00:42:17,496
Well, he's not, hon.
But Mama is. Okay?

484
00:42:23,794 --> 00:42:25,712
Eat your cake.

485
00:42:28,757 --> 00:42:31,426
- Hello.
- This is Kenneth King.

486
00:42:31,510 --> 00:42:35,055
- Mr. King.
- I imagine you,

487
00:42:35,264 --> 00:42:38,100
heard about
my daughter's disappearance?

488
00:42:38,141 --> 00:42:39,852
- Yes.
- Well...

489
00:42:39,935 --> 00:42:41,895
Mrs. Wilson,
I don't believe in what you do.

490
00:42:41,979 --> 00:42:43,939
I'll just be
straight with you.

491
00:42:44,022 --> 00:42:48,569
Not only that, I don't like it. But
we've got to the end of the road...

492
00:42:48,610 --> 00:42:52,239
and our investigation looked under
every rock there is to look under,

493
00:42:52,281 --> 00:42:55,742
and we'd like you to tell us
what you can to help us.

494
00:42:55,784 --> 00:42:59,246
Now, no hocus-pocus
and chanting and carrying on.

495
00:42:59,329 --> 00:43:03,208
We know you talk to a lot of folks,
know a lot of folks' business.

496
00:43:03,292 --> 00:43:07,254
You might have heard
something or something.

497
00:43:07,337 --> 00:43:09,131
The only thing we know is,

498
00:43:09,214 --> 00:43:13,093
one of Sheriff Johnson's men
found my daughter's car...

499
00:43:13,135 --> 00:43:16,263
sitting out on the parking lot
of that honky-tonk called AyJay's.

500
00:43:16,346 --> 00:43:19,308
But nobody that was there
on Saturday night...

501
00:43:19,349 --> 00:43:21,643
admits to having seen her.

502
00:43:21,727 --> 00:43:25,981
So I'm afraid she might have been
kidnapped or something?

503
00:43:27,649 --> 00:43:30,819
Oh, Mr. King,
I'm... I'm sorry.

504
00:43:30,903 --> 00:43:33,822
I don't know anything about
your daughter's disappearance.

505
00:43:33,864 --> 00:43:36,366
I think
we were just hoping...

506
00:43:37,534 --> 00:43:39,995
Is there anything
you can tell us?

507
00:43:40,078 --> 00:43:42,456
I could read for you.

508
00:43:43,874 --> 00:43:47,336
But that... that's
about all I could do.

509
00:43:47,419 --> 00:43:50,047
I need you
to cut the cards for me.

510
00:44:00,307 --> 00:44:02,226
Oh, boy.

511
00:44:08,065 --> 00:44:10,067
Thank you.

512
00:44:17,032 --> 00:44:19,535
All right.
You ready?

513
00:44:21,078 --> 00:44:23,247
Okay.

514
00:44:31,046 --> 00:44:33,674
When were you
getting married again, Wayne?

515
00:44:33,715 --> 00:44:36,343
- June 20...
- We're supposed to ask questions,

516
00:44:36,385 --> 00:44:38,345
- not you.
- Shut up, Pearl! Goddamn it!

517
00:44:38,387 --> 00:44:40,347
Look, I have a hard time
concentrating...

518
00:44:40,389 --> 00:44:43,016
with more than one person
in the room.

519
00:44:43,058 --> 00:44:47,062
Well, I'm staying right here. I'm
the law, and I need to hear this.

520
00:44:47,145 --> 00:44:50,232
Please, ma'am, just...

521
00:44:50,315 --> 00:44:51,650
just try to tell us
what you see.

522
00:44:51,650 --> 00:44:52,901
just try to tell us
what you see.

523
00:44:52,943 --> 00:44:55,737
I'm trying.

524
00:44:55,779 --> 00:44:57,948
All right.

525
00:45:16,383 --> 00:45:18,343
All right,
all I'm picking up...

526
00:45:18,427 --> 00:45:22,556
it's like a...
it's a fence.

527
00:45:22,598 --> 00:45:25,893
Like a split rail fence.

528
00:45:25,934 --> 00:45:28,770
Do you know how many fences
there are in this county?

529
00:45:30,272 --> 00:45:33,233
And some pillars, like,
with an opening going through.

530
00:45:38,280 --> 00:45:42,117
And there's lots of white flowers.
I can... I...

531
00:45:42,159 --> 00:45:46,830
Yes. And,
is that where Jessie is?

532
00:45:58,383 --> 00:46:02,930
Well, that's... that's, all I'm...
all I'm seeing.

533
00:46:03,013 --> 00:46:06,391
This is just mishmash. I told you
this wouldn't lead to nothing.

534
00:46:06,475 --> 00:46:09,436
You're right. It won't.
I can't concentrate.

535
00:46:11,146 --> 00:46:15,234
- I can't do this now. I'm sorry.
- Please, ma'am.

536
00:46:15,317 --> 00:46:17,319
I really do hope
you find your daughter.

537
00:46:17,402 --> 00:46:21,490
But I'm... I'm just not the person
to help you with this.

538
00:49:03,777 --> 00:49:05,779
Hey, Butch.

539
00:49:39,104 --> 00:49:41,023
And it was horrible.

540
00:49:41,106 --> 00:49:44,026
But that same chain that was wrapped
around her when she was floatin',

541
00:49:44,109 --> 00:49:49,198
you know, up in my tree, it was the
same chain that I had in my dream.

542
00:49:49,281 --> 00:49:52,284
- I don't know. I just thought...
- Dave?

543
00:49:54,786 --> 00:49:57,164
Yes, sir?

544
00:49:57,206 --> 00:49:59,208
I could have sworn there
was an eclair in there.

545
00:49:59,249 --> 00:50:02,419
I didn't get it.

546
00:50:04,505 --> 00:50:07,216
Tim was in
a little earlier.

547
00:50:10,552 --> 00:50:12,346
So you saw all this
in a dream?

548
00:50:12,387 --> 00:50:14,348
It wasn't just a dream.

549
00:50:14,389 --> 00:50:16,475
I don't investigate
somebody's dream.

550
00:50:18,018 --> 00:50:20,062
I think she's dead, Sheriff.

551
00:50:20,145 --> 00:50:23,190
And I think she's in a pond.

552
00:50:23,232 --> 00:50:26,735
What do you know about this
you ain't telling me?

553
00:50:26,819 --> 00:50:30,030
You can get in serious
trouble with holding information.

554
00:50:30,072 --> 00:50:32,157
Does it sound like
a place you know?

555
00:50:32,241 --> 00:50:34,201
Yeah,
a bunch of places I know.

556
00:50:34,243 --> 00:50:37,496
Split rail fence, a pond,
a stretch of woods.

557
00:50:37,579 --> 00:50:40,207
- Every raw bone ol' boy got that.
- What about the fiddler?

558
00:50:40,249 --> 00:50:43,293
Well,

559
00:50:43,377 --> 00:50:45,754
ol' Tommy Lee Ballard
plays a fiddle.

560
00:50:45,838 --> 00:50:48,465
But he wouldn't kill nobody.
I've known him since he's a kid.

561
00:50:48,549 --> 00:50:52,052
No, no, it's not the fiddler.
Who are his neighbors?

562
00:50:52,094 --> 00:50:56,014
Well, his closest neighbor
would be...

563
00:50:57,266 --> 00:51:00,102
Well, let me see here.
I guess...

564
00:51:00,143 --> 00:51:04,398
Well, his property borders,
Donnie Barksdale's place.

565
00:51:05,774 --> 00:51:08,110
Do you know
Donnie Barksdale?

566
00:51:10,237 --> 00:51:12,239
Ma'am?

567
00:51:19,121 --> 00:51:21,373
Tim! On the gate!

568
00:51:22,749 --> 00:51:24,668
You did get
a search warrant, didn't you?

569
00:51:24,751 --> 00:51:26,670
I want everything
to be legal and proper.

570
00:51:26,753 --> 00:51:29,131
Didn't have to.
Got permission from the owner.

571
00:51:29,173 --> 00:51:32,467
Donnie Barksdale
gave you permission...

572
00:51:32,509 --> 00:51:36,096
His wife did.
I told her it was routine.

573
00:51:36,138 --> 00:51:38,473
We're checking all the ponds
in the county.

574
00:51:38,515 --> 00:51:40,684
Donnie's gone fishing today.

575
00:51:57,201 --> 00:51:59,745
Excuse me. Sheriff Johnson?

576
00:51:59,828 --> 00:52:03,665
- How much longer y'all gonna be?
- Long as it takes.

577
00:52:03,707 --> 00:52:07,127
All right. You just said you're
gonna be a few minutes.

578
00:52:07,169 --> 00:52:09,546
And we're
going on two hours.

579
00:52:09,630 --> 00:52:12,633
Hey, Pearl!
I think I got something!

580
00:52:41,870 --> 00:52:45,082
False alarm.
It's just an old bicycle.

581
00:52:48,585 --> 00:52:51,255
None of y'all brought a Thermos
of coffee out here?

582
00:53:14,778 --> 00:53:16,864
That day at school.

583
00:53:18,198 --> 00:53:21,118
You looked kind of strange
at me and Jessica.

584
00:53:21,201 --> 00:53:23,662
Did you think
something bad then?

585
00:53:34,298 --> 00:53:36,758
Shit.
Come on.

586
00:53:38,051 --> 00:53:41,054
- Donnie, he called. I told him...
- Pearl!

587
00:53:41,096 --> 00:53:43,182
Shut your mouth!

588
00:53:43,265 --> 00:53:45,350
Goddamn it, Pearl,
what are you doing on my property?

589
00:53:45,434 --> 00:53:48,854
I'm on Sheriff's business, Donnie.
I got permission from your wife.

590
00:53:48,937 --> 00:53:50,856
You think I let that
little ninny talk for me?

591
00:53:52,774 --> 00:53:55,444
How'd your arm
get all scratched up?

592
00:53:57,696 --> 00:54:01,241
Stray cat. She didn't like it
when I killed her.

593
00:54:01,283 --> 00:54:04,661
- Now what brought you here?
- Just routine investigation.

594
00:54:04,745 --> 00:54:06,955
We're checking
all the ponds in the county.

595
00:54:14,588 --> 00:54:18,008
- I knew it was you.
- No! You!

596
00:54:21,803 --> 00:54:25,349
Hey! I'm on County business,
Donnie. Don't fool with me.

597
00:54:25,432 --> 00:54:28,185
- Hey, Pearl!
- What?

598
00:54:28,268 --> 00:54:31,188
- You need to take a look at this.
- Watch him.

599
00:54:31,271 --> 00:54:34,274
Hault up, boys!

600
00:54:42,324 --> 00:54:45,410
- It's her!
- Donnie?

601
00:54:48,288 --> 00:54:51,667
Get those hooks
out of my baby!

602
00:54:51,708 --> 00:54:54,878
- Get her off them hooks!
- Cuff him!

603
00:54:54,962 --> 00:54:58,257
- No! No!
- Mr. King!

604
00:55:00,676 --> 00:55:03,804
- No!
- Get an ambulance!

605
00:55:03,846 --> 00:55:05,806
I think he's
having a heart attack!

606
00:55:05,848 --> 00:55:08,433
- I didn't do this!
- Get him out of here!

607
00:55:08,517 --> 00:55:10,686
This ain't right!
Pearl!

608
00:55:10,727 --> 00:55:15,023
Bitch! Bitch!
Bitch! Pearl!

609
00:55:29,121 --> 00:55:31,415
Come in.

610
00:55:34,334 --> 00:55:36,253
Somebody might
come in here.

611
00:55:36,336 --> 00:55:39,047
I guess you better
fuck me fast.

612
00:55:39,089 --> 00:55:42,009
You want some coffee?
Mrs. Wilson?

613
00:55:44,761 --> 00:55:47,014
You want some coffee?

614
00:55:47,055 --> 00:55:49,349
No, thank you.

615
00:55:49,391 --> 00:55:51,351
Have a seat.

616
00:55:56,857 --> 00:55:59,151
Why... Why have you
called me here?

617
00:55:59,234 --> 00:56:02,446
Tomorrow Donnie Barksdale goes
on trial for murder...

618
00:56:02,529 --> 00:56:05,616
and I feel
that we have a powerful case.

619
00:56:05,699 --> 00:56:07,618
In fact,
today the coroner verified...

620
00:56:07,701 --> 00:56:10,037
Donnie's tissue
under the victim's fingernails.

621
00:56:10,078 --> 00:56:13,749
Now, I only have one weak link
I got to worry about.

622
00:56:13,832 --> 00:56:17,044
- What?
- You.

623
00:56:17,085 --> 00:56:21,423
You see, you're how we found out
where the victim's body was.

624
00:56:21,465 --> 00:56:24,760
And how you found out,
well,

625
00:56:24,843 --> 00:56:28,055
that might open up
a real can of worms for us.

626
00:56:28,096 --> 00:56:32,643
Psychic phenomena,
E.S.P., dreams, visions.

627
00:56:32,726 --> 00:56:34,978
The defense
could go to town on you.

628
00:56:35,062 --> 00:56:38,273
And if that's not bad enough,
I understand there was bad blood...

629
00:56:38,357 --> 00:56:41,276
between you
and Donnie Barksdale.

630
00:56:41,318 --> 00:56:43,570
Yeah.
He threatened my kids.

631
00:56:43,612 --> 00:56:47,574
That's what I heard. I also heard
that you threatened him right back.

632
00:56:47,658 --> 00:56:49,785
Told his wife
to leave him.

633
00:56:52,204 --> 00:56:54,665
Donnie's quite
a ladies' man.

634
00:56:54,748 --> 00:56:56,959
Were you involved
with him?

635
00:56:59,044 --> 00:57:01,296
- What?
- I can deal with any revelation...

636
00:57:01,380 --> 00:57:03,298
right now.

637
00:57:03,382 --> 00:57:06,301
But at the trial
there can't be any surprises.

638
00:57:07,970 --> 00:57:10,639
So, is there anything I need
to know about you or Donnie...

639
00:57:10,722 --> 00:57:13,976
or Donnie's wife
or the victim?

640
00:57:14,017 --> 00:57:16,478
No.

641
00:57:16,562 --> 00:57:18,856
Will that be all?

642
00:57:20,023 --> 00:57:21,984
Yes, ma'am.

643
00:57:24,778 --> 00:57:28,198
You know, Mr. Duncan,

644
00:57:28,282 --> 00:57:31,743
the victim had a name.

645
00:57:31,827 --> 00:57:34,496
It was Jessica King.

646
00:57:38,333 --> 00:57:39,918
Mr. Hawkins, how long have you
worked out at AyJay's?

647
00:57:39,918 --> 00:57:42,087
Mr. Hawkins, how long have you
worked out at AyJay's?

648
00:57:42,171 --> 00:57:44,089
About ten years.

649
00:57:44,173 --> 00:57:47,718
Now, were you working at AyJay's
on Saturday night, April 8?

650
00:57:47,801 --> 00:57:50,345
- Yes, sir.
- And did you see the defendant,

651
00:57:50,429 --> 00:57:54,183
- Donnie Barksdale, there that night?
- Yes, sir.

652
00:57:54,266 --> 00:57:57,019
Could you describe the circumstances
when you saw him?

653
00:57:57,060 --> 00:58:01,857
The circumstances were I come
outside to throw out some trash.

654
00:58:01,899 --> 00:58:03,859
And do you recall
what time it was?

655
00:58:03,901 --> 00:58:06,195
About midnight,
I reckon.

656
00:58:06,278 --> 00:58:09,823
Anyhow, I seen Donnie Barksdale
out there by his truck...

657
00:58:09,907 --> 00:58:13,827
havin' an argument
with this white lady.

658
00:58:13,869 --> 00:58:18,665
She scratched his arm
and he slapped the tar out of her.

659
00:58:18,707 --> 00:58:21,543
About that time,
I go back inside.

660
00:58:21,627 --> 00:58:23,962
Is this the woman
you saw with Donnie Barksdale?

661
00:58:24,046 --> 00:58:27,257
- Yes, sir.
- Your Honor, let the record show...

662
00:58:27,341 --> 00:58:31,345
that I've just shown Mr. Hawkins
a photograph of Jessica King.

663
00:58:33,847 --> 00:58:39,019
You just said that your attention
was drawn to the defendant's pond.

664
00:58:40,354 --> 00:58:43,357
Drawn in...
Well, drawn in what way?

665
00:58:44,733 --> 00:58:47,569
Me, Wayne Collins
and Kenneth King...

666
00:58:47,611 --> 00:58:49,571
went to see a woman,
name of Annie Wilson.

667
00:58:49,613 --> 00:58:52,074
What made you think this woman
would be able to help you?

668
00:58:52,115 --> 00:58:57,913
Well, word around town
was that she was a...

669
00:59:00,833 --> 00:59:04,878
- Well, I don't know the right word.
- Isn't it fortune-teller?

670
00:59:06,672 --> 00:59:08,924
- I guess so.
- What did this fortune-teller see...

671
00:59:09,007 --> 00:59:11,969
when she looked into
her little crystal ball?

672
00:59:12,010 --> 00:59:16,849
Well, she didn't have no ball.
She had these, special cards.

673
00:59:16,932 --> 00:59:20,185
What did she see when she looked
into her little special cards?

674
00:59:20,269 --> 00:59:22,521
She didn't actually
see nothing then.

675
00:59:22,604 --> 00:59:26,108
But next day,
she come to see me and...

676
00:59:26,191 --> 00:59:28,068
told me
she had this dream.

677
00:59:28,152 --> 00:59:31,155
- She had a dream?
- Yes, sir.

678
00:59:31,238 --> 00:59:35,450
She'd seen this pond and it looked
a lot like Donnie Barksdale's and...

679
00:59:37,035 --> 00:59:39,621
then she woke up
from her dream...

680
00:59:39,705 --> 00:59:42,749
and she went outside
and looked up in this tree.

681
00:59:45,794 --> 00:59:47,796
I'm all ears.

682
00:59:51,800 --> 00:59:54,887
She seen Jessica King...

683
00:59:54,970 --> 00:59:57,598
floatin' in the tree,

684
00:59:57,681 --> 01:00:00,476
half-naked, with a chain
wrapped around her.

685
01:00:00,517 --> 01:00:02,936
Floatin' around a tree?

686
01:00:04,396 --> 01:00:06,356
Yes, sir.

687
01:00:07,858 --> 01:00:09,818
Floatin' in a tree,

688
01:00:09,902 --> 01:00:11,987
half-naked,

689
01:00:13,906 --> 01:00:16,200
with a chain
wrapped around her.

690
01:00:16,241 --> 01:00:18,577
Thank you, Sheriff.

691
01:00:20,078 --> 01:00:22,581
That little squirrel,
Weems, is just mean and skinny.

692
01:00:22,664 --> 01:00:25,167
Never have known
a Weems worth a damn.

693
01:00:25,250 --> 01:00:27,127
Well, he was
just doing his job.

694
01:00:27,211 --> 01:00:31,048
Mrs. Wilson?
Can I talk to you for a minute?

695
01:00:31,089 --> 01:00:34,426
Just call me later on, okay?

696
01:00:34,510 --> 01:00:36,428
- Oh, okay.
- Okay, bye.

697
01:00:36,512 --> 01:00:41,141
Buddy, I got a lot on my mind.
It's not a good time, okay?

698
01:00:43,477 --> 01:00:45,395
Mrs. Wilson?

699
01:00:45,479 --> 01:00:49,525
You did tell me to do some thinkin'
and talkin'. And I've been thinkin'.

700
01:00:49,608 --> 01:00:51,401
What? What?

701
01:00:51,443 --> 01:00:55,322
Can you tell me why
I do things to myself...

702
01:00:55,405 --> 01:00:57,324
when I think
about my daddy?

703
01:00:57,407 --> 01:00:59,493
All right, well...

704
01:00:59,576 --> 01:01:03,789
Bud, you call me later, hon,
and we'll talk, all right?

705
01:01:03,872 --> 01:01:06,667
- I need to talk to you.
- Buddy.

706
01:01:06,750 --> 01:01:09,670
I've been thinking about my daddy
and I've been touching myself.

707
01:01:09,753 --> 01:01:12,673
- Touching yourself? How?
- Why do I do that?

708
01:01:12,756 --> 01:01:14,299
It's not a good time.

709
01:01:14,383 --> 01:01:17,636
- Something's bad wrong with me.
- Look, Buddy...

710
01:01:17,719 --> 01:01:20,681
And I... I keep thinking
about that blue diamond.

711
01:01:20,764 --> 01:01:24,560
You look into the blue diamond,
you won't think a negative thought.

712
01:01:24,643 --> 01:01:28,438
I promise. Now, hon, I'm going
through a hard time myself. I'm...

713
01:01:28,480 --> 01:01:31,775
I just... I can't talk
to you now, okay?

714
01:01:35,112 --> 01:01:37,739
You're gonna burn
in hell, Annie Wilson!

715
01:01:48,417 --> 01:01:51,587
Now, Mike, I know you skipped
school and went to that trial.

716
01:01:51,670 --> 01:01:54,756
- How'd you know?
- A little bird told me.

