I will. I wouldn't blame you.

962
01:17:05,167 --> 01:17:07,669
But I need you
to read for me.

963
01:17:15,761 --> 01:17:17,721
Give me a hand.

964
01:17:20,724 --> 01:17:24,478
I feel like I can't
hold on any longer.

965
01:17:24,561 --> 01:17:29,358
I know Donnie's mean and everything,
but I feel real lost without him.

966
01:17:29,399 --> 01:17:32,402
You know, I ain't never
been on my own before.

967
01:17:32,444 --> 01:17:35,614
And I'm scared, Annie.

968
01:17:35,697 --> 01:17:39,451
You don't need to be scared, hon.
You'll be fine.

969
01:17:41,578 --> 01:17:43,622
You see that
in the cards?

970
01:17:43,705 --> 01:17:46,500
Right through here.

971
01:17:46,583 --> 01:17:49,795
But can you see
what... what I'm thinking?

972
01:17:49,878 --> 01:17:53,090
Can you see that
in the cards?

973
01:17:53,173 --> 01:17:55,133
What do you mean?

974
01:17:55,217 --> 01:17:57,553
Well,

975
01:17:57,636 --> 01:18:02,641
I've been thinking
some real bad, bad thoughts.

976
01:18:02,724 --> 01:18:05,686
Unchristian thoughts.

977
01:18:05,769 --> 01:18:08,147
Like what?

978
01:18:08,230 --> 01:18:09,606
Like...

979
01:18:11,483 --> 01:18:14,486
I'm glad that girl's dead.
Jessica.

980
01:18:14,570 --> 01:18:17,614
She was messin' around with my
husband and deserved what she got.

981
01:18:17,698 --> 01:18:19,616
No one deserves that.

982
01:18:19,700 --> 01:18:23,162
Like I said,
I know it's unchristian.

983
01:18:29,626 --> 01:18:33,672
What? What, are you
seeing something bad?

984
01:18:36,091 --> 01:18:38,010
I don't know.

985
01:18:43,807 --> 01:18:46,185
It's not clear.

986
01:20:22,865 --> 01:20:25,200
Fuck you!

987
01:21:06,241 --> 01:21:08,202
Wayne?

988
01:21:19,171 --> 01:21:21,089
Wayne?

989
01:21:41,777 --> 01:21:44,279
It's not normally
like this.

990
01:21:49,785 --> 01:21:53,330
You need
to lie down.

991
01:21:53,413 --> 01:21:55,457
I'm really not sleepy.

992
01:21:55,541 --> 01:21:59,044
I think if you sleep,
you'll feel better.

993
01:22:12,224 --> 01:22:14,184
Thank you, Annie.

994
01:22:15,644 --> 01:22:18,522
Oh. It's okay.

995
01:22:40,419 --> 01:22:42,337
Wayne.

996
01:22:44,423 --> 01:22:47,426
I don't think
this is a good idea.

997
01:22:49,136 --> 01:22:51,054
No.

998
01:22:53,140 --> 01:22:55,058
It's not.

999
01:22:57,394 --> 01:23:00,355
I just thought we could
forget all this for a while.

1000
01:23:02,816 --> 01:23:05,027
You want to,
don't you?

1001
01:23:21,585 --> 01:23:24,171
I know there's
something between us.

1002
01:23:30,302 --> 01:23:32,221
I can't.

1003
01:23:33,931 --> 01:23:36,433
I guess
I still feel married.

1004
01:23:39,228 --> 01:23:41,188
You're not, though.

1005
01:23:44,066 --> 01:23:46,902
- He's gone.
- I know.

1006
01:23:48,195 --> 01:23:50,531
You gotta learn
to deal with that.

1007
01:23:53,325 --> 01:23:57,663
The same way I gotta learn to deal
with the fact that Jessica's gone.

1008
01:24:03,085 --> 01:24:05,045
She's dead.

1009
01:24:06,922 --> 01:24:09,424
Oh, Wayne,
I'm so sorry.

1010
01:24:11,593 --> 01:24:14,221
It's okay.

1011
01:24:14,263 --> 01:24:16,765
No, it's not okay.

1012
01:24:18,976 --> 01:24:23,814
I... I don't think
Donnie Barksdale killed her.

1013
01:24:25,774 --> 01:24:27,901
- No, no, Annie.
- I'm really sorry.

1014
01:24:27,943 --> 01:24:30,362
I can't... I can't do this.
It's finished.

1015
01:24:30,445 --> 01:24:33,824
I know. I wanna let
that bastard rot in jail.

1016
01:24:33,907 --> 01:24:36,577
- But he's guilty.
- No, Wayne.

1017
01:24:36,660 --> 01:24:38,620
I see it.

1018
01:24:41,790 --> 01:24:44,084
I see he didn't do it.

1019
01:24:47,629 --> 01:24:52,092
- Do you see who did?
- I'm trying, but I... I...

1020
01:24:52,176 --> 01:24:54,136
I don't know yet.

1021
01:24:54,178 --> 01:24:56,889
What are we gonna do?

1022
01:24:58,348 --> 01:25:01,226
Well, if I had
a piece of clothing...

1023
01:25:01,310 --> 01:25:05,939
or maybe I could go
out to the pond or see if I...

1024
01:25:07,524 --> 01:25:12,196
It's not over.
Jesus.

1025
01:26:54,965 --> 01:26:56,800
Come on in.

1026
01:27:00,679 --> 01:27:04,475
Well,
what brings you out here?

1027
01:27:06,018 --> 01:27:08,896
Well, I'll just come
straight out and say it.

1028
01:27:08,979 --> 01:27:11,356
I don't think Donnie Barksdale
killed Jessica King.

1029
01:27:11,440 --> 01:27:13,400
Well, sure he did.
It was an open-and-shut case.

1030
01:27:13,484 --> 01:27:15,027
I'm telling you he didn't.

1031
01:27:15,110 --> 01:27:17,738
The person that killed Jessica
is still out there someplace.

1032
01:27:17,821 --> 01:27:20,032
What's the deal? The Barksdales
been threatening you?

1033
01:27:20,115 --> 01:27:22,284
- No.
- I'll talk to Pearl Johnson.

1034
01:27:22,367 --> 01:27:25,871
This has nothing to do
with the Barksdales. Listen.

1035
01:27:25,954 --> 01:27:27,915
I know that Donnie
didn't kill Jessica...

1036
01:27:27,998 --> 01:27:30,542
the same way that I knew
that her body was in his pond.

1037
01:27:30,626 --> 01:27:34,630
And do you know
who did kill her?

1038
01:27:37,508 --> 01:27:39,426
No.

1039
01:27:39,510 --> 01:27:41,720
So, what do you care?
The son of a bitch is in jail.

1040
01:27:41,804 --> 01:27:44,515
I got a warning today.

1041
01:27:44,598 --> 01:27:47,392
I think somebody is
gonna try and kill me.

1042
01:27:47,476 --> 01:27:49,394
What do you
want me to do?

1043
01:27:49,478 --> 01:27:51,396
Reopen the case and find out
who really did it.

1044
01:27:51,480 --> 01:27:54,316
- I can't. He's been convicted.
- Well, you can talk to somebody.

1045
01:27:54,358 --> 01:27:56,318
I've got no basis to open this case.
I'd look like a fool.

1046
01:27:56,360 --> 01:27:59,363
I don't give a damn
how you look.

1047
01:27:59,404 --> 01:28:01,490
Now, you listen to me.

1048
01:28:01,532 --> 01:28:04,868
I know you had
an affair with Jessica.

1049
01:28:04,910 --> 01:28:07,955
So how do you think you're
gonna look if people find out...

1050
01:28:08,038 --> 01:28:11,792
you had sex with the victim
the night before she was killed?

1051
01:28:36,733 --> 01:28:38,819
Do you want money?

1052
01:28:41,738 --> 01:28:45,159
No. I want you
to reopen the case.

1053
01:28:48,453 --> 01:28:51,832
There's a saying about
letting sleeping dogs lie.

1054
01:28:51,915 --> 01:28:55,794
You think you're in danger now?
Look at it logically.

1055
01:28:55,878 --> 01:28:59,506
The real danger begins if this case
gets reopened and someone starts...

1056
01:28:59,590 --> 01:29:02,050
worrying that you're gonna have
another one of your damn dreams.

1057
01:29:15,772 --> 01:29:17,733
All I know is,
the wrong man's in jail.

1058
01:29:17,774 --> 01:29:20,944
I don't care how awful he is.
And I helped put him there.

1059
01:29:23,280 --> 01:29:25,616
I can't live
with something like that.

1060
01:29:27,451 --> 01:29:30,954
So you find a way
to reopen this case, sir.

1061
01:29:31,038 --> 01:29:32,956
Or I will.

1062
01:30:08,992 --> 01:30:11,328
Buddy!

1063
01:30:18,669 --> 01:30:21,130
Buddy, I'm here if you...

1064
01:30:48,073 --> 01:30:50,200
- Hello.
- Hi, Miss Francis. I'm back.

1065
01:30:50,284 --> 01:30:52,202
- Good.
- How are the boys?

1066
01:30:52,286 --> 01:30:54,746
They're fine. They went to sleep.
You want me to bring 'em over?

1067
01:30:54,830 --> 01:30:57,833
No. No. Listen.

1068
01:30:57,875 --> 01:31:00,169
Could we stay over
your house tonight?

1069
01:31:00,210 --> 01:31:03,380
- Sure you can. You all right?
- Oh, yeah, I'm fine.

1070
01:31:03,464 --> 01:31:06,383
Come over. I'll make a bed for you.

1071
01:31:06,425 --> 01:31:09,011
- All right. I'm just gonna lock up.
- Okay, doll.

1072
01:31:09,094 --> 01:31:11,054
- Okay, thank you.
- Bye-bye.

1073
01:31:26,820 --> 01:31:28,739
Buddy!

1074
01:31:31,700 --> 01:31:35,078
Oh! Did you see
Buddy Cole?

1075
01:31:35,120 --> 01:31:38,207
Buddy? No. I thought he was
at the hospital over in Benton?

1076
01:31:38,248 --> 01:31:41,627
- Oh, he is. Maybe I imagined it.
- Are you okay?

1077
01:31:41,710 --> 01:31:43,629
I don't know
what I'm gonna do.

1078
01:31:43,712 --> 01:31:48,175
Ever since you told me what you told
me, I feel like I'm going crazy.

1079
01:31:48,258 --> 01:31:50,636
Annie, I can't stand
another night of this.

1080
01:31:50,719 --> 01:31:52,679
I need you
to read for me.

1081
01:32:01,897 --> 01:32:03,816
It's no good.

1082
01:32:05,609 --> 01:32:08,946
- Try it again.
- I can't make it happen.

1083
01:32:16,870 --> 01:32:19,081
How about
what you said today?

1084
01:32:19,164 --> 01:32:21,124
What?

1085
01:32:22,584 --> 01:32:24,503
The pond.

1086
01:32:24,586 --> 01:32:27,756
What if we did
go back out there?

1087
01:32:27,840 --> 01:32:30,801
Do you think
it might help you?

1088
01:32:30,843 --> 01:32:32,803
I... I...

1089
01:32:32,845 --> 01:32:35,389
I don't know.
Yeah. Maybe.

1090
01:32:35,472 --> 01:32:38,100
Yeah, okay. Well,
it's worth a try, right?

1091
01:32:38,183 --> 01:32:41,353
You mean tonight? No, Wayne.
I can't... I can't do that.

1092
01:32:41,436 --> 01:32:43,897
I got my kids. It's dark.

1093
01:32:43,981 --> 01:32:46,608
You know, it's... it is a pol...
it's a police matter now.

1094
01:32:46,650 --> 01:32:49,236
How long do you think
that's gonna take, Annie?

1095
01:32:49,319 --> 01:32:53,115
It's gonna sit on somebody's desk
for months. Nothing's gonna happen.

1096
01:32:53,157 --> 01:32:55,242
It's over for them. They've got
their man. It's up to us.

1097
01:32:55,325 --> 01:32:58,745
I know that, Wayne. But I'm
telling you, I don't see anything.

1098
01:33:03,959 --> 01:33:06,253
I can't keep running
from things.

1099
01:33:56,720 --> 01:33:59,556
Maybe if you just
sort of walk around.

1100
01:33:59,640 --> 01:34:01,558
All right.

1101
01:34:43,433 --> 01:34:45,352
Oh, shoot!

1102
01:34:57,990 --> 01:35:00,159
Jeez, you all right?
You okay?

1103
01:35:00,242 --> 01:35:02,161
Yeah.

1104
01:35:05,706 --> 01:35:07,624
Yeah.

1105
01:35:42,951 --> 01:35:44,870
What are you
doing here?

1106
01:35:52,044 --> 01:35:54,046
You seeing something?

1107
01:36:03,388 --> 01:36:07,434
I've been thinking
some real bad, bad thoughts.

1108
01:36:07,518 --> 01:36:08,769
Annie?

1109
01:36:08,852 --> 01:36:12,064
I'm glad that girl is dead.
Jessica.

1110
01:36:12,147 --> 01:36:15,317
She was messin' around with my
husband and deserved what she got.

1111
01:36:19,238 --> 01:36:22,783
I couldn't sleep.
Met the girls for a drink.

1112
01:36:24,201 --> 01:36:26,328
Take off your clothes.

1113
01:36:32,543 --> 01:36:35,546
Aren't you taking yours off too?

1114
01:36:35,629 --> 01:36:39,341
There's a saying
about letting sleeping dogs lie.

1115
01:36:40,551 --> 01:36:44,680
You just fucked him,
didn't you?

1116
01:36:46,974 --> 01:36:49,893
Donnie Barksdale?

1117
01:36:51,061 --> 01:36:53,021
So?

1118
01:36:53,063 --> 01:36:56,733
Why would you do this to me?
I love you.

1119
01:36:56,817 --> 01:36:58,986
Maybe I wanted to be
with a man for a change.

1120
01:36:59,069 --> 01:37:01,488
- Watch your mouth.
- You watch your mouth. Fuck you!

1121
01:37:01,572 --> 01:37:04,366
- I'm sorry.
- We're through.

1122
01:37:04,408 --> 01:37:07,161
I don't like being spied on.

1123
01:37:07,244 --> 01:37:10,497
The only reason I'm with you
is 'cause my daddy likes you.

1124
01:37:13,083 --> 01:37:15,002
You horrible little bitch!

1125
01:37:15,085 --> 01:37:17,838
I'll show you a bitch if you
don't let go of me. Let go!

1126
01:37:39,943 --> 01:37:42,279
- I think we better go back.
- Nothing's coming to you?

1127
01:37:44,281 --> 01:37:46,241
No.

1128
01:37:46,283 --> 01:37:48,535
Nothing.

1129
01:37:57,461 --> 01:37:59,379
You know.

1130
01:38:02,257 --> 01:38:06,053
I knew if I got you close enough
to it that you'd see it.

1131
01:38:06,136 --> 01:38:09,473
- Wayne, I told you...
- No, no. It's okay.

1132
01:38:09,556 --> 01:38:11,767
I swear to God, Annie,
it's okay. It's okay.

1133
01:38:11,809 --> 01:38:13,811
I wanted you to.
I swear to God.

1134
01:38:13,894 --> 01:38:17,856
I wanted you to see it so bad.
I mean, that's why we're here.

1135
01:38:17,940 --> 01:38:20,484
I'm not some killer, Annie.
I'm not.

1136
01:38:20,567 --> 01:38:23,821
You don't... I mean, do you know
what it was like with her?

1137
01:38:23,904 --> 01:38:27,574
She was so fucking hurtful
and spiteful and all of it...

1138
01:38:27,658 --> 01:38:29,243
Wayne, I'm not gonna...

1139
01:38:29,326 --> 01:38:31,995
But all of it just happened
in this flash of a moment.

1140
01:38:32,079 --> 01:38:35,541
- Wayne, I...
- Listen to me. I'm a good man.

1141
01:38:35,624 --> 01:38:38,877
If it had been you instead of her,
none of this would have happened.

1142
01:38:38,961 --> 01:38:41,130
Wayne.

1143
01:38:44,007 --> 01:38:45,968
It's all right, you know?

1144
01:38:46,009 --> 01:38:49,263
I won't... I won't tell.

1145
01:38:52,349 --> 01:38:55,477
I won't...
I won't tell anybody.

1146
01:38:57,187 --> 01:38:59,231
No, Annie...

1147
01:40:12,888 --> 01:40:15,224
You all right, Mrs. Wilson?

1148
01:41:04,106 --> 01:41:07,985
I thought you were supposed to
be in the hospital.

1149
01:41:08,068 --> 01:41:11,822
I escaped, Mrs. Wilson.

1150
01:41:11,905 --> 01:41:14,283
I'm free.

1151
01:41:15,701 --> 01:41:18,620
Buddy, I'm so sorry
I wasn't there for you.

1152
01:41:20,330 --> 01:41:23,375
- I should've...
- Now, don't you say another word.

1153
01:41:26,587 --> 01:41:30,299
You was the only one
that was a friend to me.

1154
01:41:31,800 --> 01:41:33,760
And I love you.

1155
01:41:37,264 --> 01:41:40,893
You're the soul
of this town, Mrs. Wilson.

1156
01:41:40,976 --> 01:41:45,105
And you just need to keep doing
what you're doing.

1157
01:42:00,454 --> 01:42:02,372
I washed it.

1158
01:42:17,638 --> 01:42:20,015
Will you come back
into town with me?

1159
01:42:20,098 --> 01:42:22,017
Yeah.

1160
01:42:37,866 --> 01:42:41,203
You know you're
gonna have to go back.

1161
01:42:43,038 --> 01:42:45,624
Yes, ma'am, I know.

1162
01:43:18,574 --> 01:43:20,534
Can I have your keys,
ma'am?

1163
01:43:43,182 --> 01:43:44,266
Well,

1164
01:43:44,475 --> 01:43:47,728
I just talked to Wayne.

1165
01:43:47,769 --> 01:43:50,772
He pretty much admitted
to everything.

1166
01:43:50,856 --> 01:43:55,235
I've known that boy
half my life.

1167
01:43:58,906 --> 01:44:01,825
It just goes to show,
you can know somebody and...

1168
01:44:05,579 --> 01:44:07,498
not know 'em.

1169
01:44:10,125 --> 01:44:13,545
How's his...
How's his head?

1170
01:44:13,629 --> 01:44:15,756
Well, you put
a pretty good dent in it.

1171
01:44:15,798 --> 01:44:18,717
Oh, no, Sheriff,
I told...

1172
01:44:18,801 --> 01:44:20,969
I told the deputy
it wasn't me who did that.

1173
01:44:21,053 --> 01:44:24,097
It was...
It was Buddy Cole. He saved me.

1174
01:44:24,181 --> 01:44:27,226
- No, ma'am. It weren't Buddy.
- Well, yes, it was.

1175
01:44:27,309 --> 01:44:30,813
- Why don't you just ask Wayne?
- I did.

1176
01:44:30,896 --> 01:44:33,232
He don't remember
what happened.

1177
01:44:33,315 --> 01:44:35,567
Head injuries is funny.

1178
01:44:35,651 --> 01:44:40,781
- I'm telling you, it was Buddy Cole.
- What I'm tryin' to say is,

1179
01:44:40,823 --> 01:44:43,158
it couldn't have been Buddy.

1180
01:44:43,242 --> 01:44:45,702
I... I just called up
at the State Hospital.

1181
01:44:45,786 --> 01:44:49,081
- He told me he escaped.
- Ma'am.

1182
01:44:51,041 --> 01:44:53,168
Buddy Cole is dead.

1183
01:44:55,629 --> 01:44:58,132
He hanged himself
in the shower room...

1184
01:44:59,758 --> 01:45:01,677
6:00 this evening.

